CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 5, 1966, pg. 1B reads: "Royal Pair - One of the highlights of the Dynamic Danettes' Mardi Gras, was the presentation of a king and queen who reigned over festivities. Mrs. Lydia Phillips was crowned "Queen" and Thomas Alexander, "King."
TitMainTitle: "Queen" Lydia Phillips and "King" Thomas Alexander, walking through ballroom of Roosevelt Hotel for Danettes Mardi Gras Ball
